HEADWORD: Tetrachotomous
<hw>Tet`ra*chot"o*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>te`tracha</grk> in four parts + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a division by fours; separated into four
parts or series, or into series of fours.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetracid</ent>⟦br⟧
